Key Match Events: Atlanta Braves rallied to beat Toronto Blue Jays 4-3 in the 11th inning
Sean Murphy's infield ground ball scored a sliding Eli White in the 11th inning
Braves got another brilliant outing from left-hander Chris Sale
White had two crucial hits after entering the game as a defensive replacement at second base
Trailing 2-1 in the 9th, White reached first on a bouncing ball up the middle for a single
Matt Olson then lofted a long fly ball to left, easily scoring White for the sacrifice fly that tied it
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Braves now have 12 extra-inning wins, which leads the big leagues
The Braves took two of three games from the Blue Jays
Others: The Braves are tied with the New York Mets for the final wild card in a tight National League playoff race
The Braves are missing 2B Ozzie Albies (left wrist fracture)
